com.nokia.places

Interface Place


  • public interface Place
    This interface represents a set of data about a physical place.

    A Place acts as a container for various information about a place, which itself is a point of interest such as a popular restaurant, a park, or someone's home.

    Note: A Place can contain attributes, collections of media about the place, and key-value pairs of related places.


    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - Location, Nokia's Restful Places API - Base Attributes, ExtendedAttribute, Nokia's Restful Places API - Extended Attributes, Nokia's Restful Places API - Media collections, Nokia's Restful Places API - Related Places

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        This method retrieves the unique identifier of the place.

        Applications that want to keep a reference to a place should store the place identifier, so that they can link to the place resource.

        Returns:
        The place identifier.

      • getExtendedAttributes

        java.lang.String[] getExtendedAttributes()
        This method retrieves additional information about a place, an extensible collection of attributes that can include:
        • payment
        • openingHours
        • annualClosings
        • nearestLandmark
        • languagesSpoken
        • availableParking
        • smoking
        • disabledAccess
        Returns:
        An array of key-value extended attributes for the place.

      • getRelated

        java.util.Hashtable getRelated()
        This method retrieves the related places that might also interest a user (where available).

        An array is keyed by a title of the related places (for example, "Nearby"), while the associated value is a link to a page of related places.

        Note: If there are no related places, the related attribute is not present.

        Returns:
        An array of related places links (could be null).
